                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Rectangular stone altar, with hollowed-out entabulature to receive text. There is a fracture running from right to left in the bottom half of the stone, and the two fractured pieces have been reassembled. Other than the fracture, and rough top edge, the inscription in generally in good condition.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">Marble</material> <!-- DEFAULT VALUE -->
                                    <objectType ana="#object.altar" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html">Altar</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">40</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">28</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">8</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.complete"/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>The text occupies the whole entabulature, and is roughly centered (except for line 5 which is slightly left aligned).</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The letters are well formed and the text is mostly legible with a few exceptions for those letters obscured by the fracture. The size of the letters appears to decrease with each successive line, although within each line the letters are roughly the same size and height. There is a tall "T" in line 6. Use of triangular interpuncts. The interpunct between "V" and "S" in line 5 is restored given the fracture in the stone.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line6">Lines 1–6</locus>
